 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "OtherTransportAdvisor ⊣ Other Transport Equipment Plant Operations
 Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for the residual 'other transport
 equipment n.e.c.' vertical -- animal-drawn vehicles (carts, wagons,
 carriages) and hand-propelled vehicles (hand-carts, hand-trucks,
 wheelbarrows, rickshaws, sledges, toboggans, pushcarts) assembled on
 a chassis/axle/wheel/body assembly line and inspected on structural/
 load test benches -- distinct from bicycles and invalid carriages
 (wheelchairs/mobility scooters), which are ISIC 3092. Not direct
 assembly-line-equipment control authority and not safety-
 certification authority. Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Twelve concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct assembly-line-equipment control), permanent
 equipment-actuate block, permanent safety-certification-authority
 block (this actor never self-issues a transport-equipment safety/
 roadworthiness certification mark), independent equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-quantity recompute against the batch's own
 logged production quantity, double-schedule guard, product-category
 validation, weight-capacity plausibility validation, and assembly-
 defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging
 (materials-safety/structural-integrity) ALWAYS escalates to a human
 plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to
 auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
